# Database: Use Drizzle ORM

All database interactions must use the Drizzle schema and query builder. Never write raw SQL or use any other query method.

## Schema

Tables are defined in [src/db/schema.ts](mdc:src/db/schema.ts). The two tables are:
- `decks` — belongs to a `clerkUserId`, has `title` and `description`
- `cards` — belongs to a `deckId` (cascade deletes), has `front` and `back`

## DB Client

Import the `db` instance from [src/db/index.ts](mdc:src/db/index.ts):

```ts
import { db } from "@/db";
import { decks, cards } from "@/db/schema";
```

## Query Patterns

```ts
// ✅ Query with Drizzle
const userDecks = await db.select().from(decks).where(eq(decks.clerkUserId, userId));

// ✅ Insert
await db.insert(cards).values({ deckId, front, back });

// ✅ Update
await db.update(decks).set({ title }).where(eq(decks.id, deckId));

// ✅ Delete
await db.delete(cards).where(eq(cards.id, cardId));

// ❌ Never use raw SQL
await sql`SELECT * FROM decks`;
```

## Relations

Use Drizzle's `with` for joins instead of multiple queries:

```ts
const deckWithCards = await db.query.decks.findFirst({
  where: eq(decks.id, deckId),
  with: { cards: true },
});
```
